        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Also, \"data\" seems more suitable for potentially private info, whereas it's common to store \"config\" in a public repo. Spell .add files may contain quasi-private data. (Though XDG doesn't actually comment on this.)\n\nIndeed, this was actually the reason I came up with the issue. I almost `git add`'ed my spell files. \n\n> As to implementation, it seems easiest just to prepend stdpath('data') .. 'spell' to the list of directories spellfile.c looks at (and update the documentation)? No reason to mess with adding or changing options for this.\n\nI'll try this!\n",
